{
    "name": "Blue Whale",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any ocean<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, or pod (3\u201318)<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Hold Breath (Ex)</b> A blue whale can hold its breath a number of rounds equal to 10 times its Constitution score before it risks drowning.<br/><br/><b>Powerful Tail (Ex)</b> A blue whale\u2019s massive tail deals more damage than a normal tail slap. The blue whale\u2019s tail slap is a primary attack and applies 1-1/2 times its Strength bonus to its tail slap damage.<br/><br/><b>Stun (Ex)</b> A blue whale\u2019s fluke can deliver a powerful stunning blow. A creature struck by this attack must succeed at a DC 34 Fortitude save or be dazed for 1 round. If the strike is a critical hit and the target fails its save, it is instead stunned for 1d4 rounds. The save DC is Strength-based."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The imposing blue whale is one of the largest animals in the sea, though it is generally docile toward anything it doesn\u2019t perceive as a threat. A filter-feeder, the blue whale does not look at humans or ships as potential meals, instead preferring to eat millions of tiny invertebrates known as krill, which it sucks through its baleen in massive gulps. The most dangerous thing about a blue whale, other than its sheer size, is its powerful tail, which can capsize boats and kill humanoids. These enormous mammals can be found in all of Golarion\u2019s oceans and seas. An adult blue whale is 100 feet long and weighs 200 tons."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This massive aquatic mammal has bluish-gray coloration, a wide fluke tail, and a wide mouth filled with layers of baleen.</i>",
